# Footer Customization Guide

This guide covers how to work with and customize the enhanced footer component in [components/Footer.tsx](mdc:components/Footer.tsx).

## Footer Structure

The current footer uses a modern glass-morphism design with a three-column layout:

1. Left column: Profile information, expertise areas, and social links
2. Middle column: Quick navigation and expertise tags
3. Right column: Contact card with gradient button and website info

## Key Design Elements

### Glass-Morphism Effect

The glass effect is achieved with these CSS properties:
```css
.footer-container {
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.9) 0%, rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.95) 100%);
  backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
  border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
}
```

### Animated Particles

The animated background particles are created dynamically with JavaScript:
```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  const particlesContainer = document.querySelector('.footer-particles');
  if (particlesContainer) {
    for (let i = 0; i < 30; i++) {
      const particle = document.createElement('div');
      particle.className = 'particle';
      // Set random properties
      particlesContainer.appendChild(particle);
    }
  }
}, []);
```

