## Interactive Elements

### Social Links

Social links have hover effects with labels:
```jsx
<div className="social-links">
  {socialLinks.map((link, index) => (
    <a key={index} href={link.url} className="social-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label={link.label}>
      <div className="social-icon-wrapper">
        {link.icon}
        <span className="social-hover-text">{link.label}</span>
      </div>
    </a>
  ))}
</div>
```

### Navigation Links with Icons

Navigation links include icons:
```jsx
<ul className="footer-nav-links">
  {menuLinks.map((link, index) => (
    <li key={index} className="footer-nav-item">
      <Link href={link.url} className="footer-nav-link">
        <span className="nav-link-icon">{link.icon}</span>
        <span>{link.name}</span>
      </Link>
    </li>
  ))}
</ul>
```

### Contact Button

The contact button has a gradient and hover animation:
```jsx
<a href="mailto:reyhan@example.com" className="contact-button">
  <FaEnvelope className="contact-button-icon" />
  <span>Contact Me</span>
</a>
```

## Responsive Design

The footer is fully responsive with specific styles for different breakpoints:
- Desktop: Three-column layout
- Tablet: Two-column layout with stacked right column
- Mobile: Single column with centered content

## Customization Guidelines

When customizing the footer:

1. Maintain the glass-morphism effect and overall aesthetic
2. Keep the wave divider and animated particles for visual interest
3. Ensure responsive layout works at all breakpoints
4. Preserve hover effects and animations for interactive elements
5. Use consistent icons from the React Icons library

